I"S<p>Ben, Logan, Ari, and KJ led a training in the Argonne Leading Computing Facility (ALCF) <a href="https://www.alcf.anl.gov/alcf-ai-science-training-series">AI for Science Training</a> series, in collaboration with Eliu Huerta and Venkat Vishwanath of Argonne National Laboratory. Trainees learned how to leverage modern computing environments and advanced scientific data infrastructure (DLHub, funcX and ThetaGPU) to create FAIR (Findable, Accessible, Interoperable, and Reusable) AI models and datasets. Video is available <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=X5F0XIesdfM">here</a>.</p>
